   - `~⌈a⌉φ` is in `X`, and
   - the projection of `a` on the formulas of `X` plus `~φ` is a subset of the formulas of `Y`.

This definition ensures that the relation `Rel` captures the necessary logical steps to establish the model graph properties. The use of `projection` and subset relation ensures that the logical consequences of the program `a` are correctly reflected in the transition from `X` to `Y`.

